muCNV: Multi-sample SV caller for large-scale WGS data

Feb. 28, 2018
(c) Goo Jun

muCNV has two-stage model for multi-sample SV calling: 1) From candiate list
of SVs, generate sample-level summary from CRAM/BAM files 2) Multi-sample
genotyping from summary files.


1. Generate sample-by-sample summary from list of candidate SVs

$ mucnv -s <sample ID> -v <VCF> -f <GRCh file> -b <BAM/CRAM file> -o <output prefix>

GRCh file for human reference genome build 38 is provided in resources/GRCh38.gc

Required parameters:
   -s <string>,  --sample <string>
     Sample ID

   -f <string>,  --gcFile <string>
     File containing GC content information

   -v <string>,  --vcf <string>
     VCF file containing candidate SVs

   -o <string>,  --out <string>
     Prefix for sample-level summary VCF file

   -b <string>,  --bam <string>
     Input BAM/CRAM file name


2. Multi-sample genotyping

$ mucnv -g -i <input.index> -o <output prefix> -r <region>

Required parameters:

   -i <string>,  --index <string>
     List file containing list of sample-level VCF files, should be bgzipped/tabixed

   -g,  --genotype
     Switch argument to generate multi-sample genotype

   -o <string>,  --out <string>
     Prefix for output VCF file

   -r <string> --region <string>
     Genomic region to genotype, chr:start-end (inclusive)

For full list of options:
$ ./muCNV -h 



